long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: Despite the recent warnings, I ran dnf distro-sync within GNOME. That crashed X and nuked the running upgrade.
Since I keep my machine up-to-date, this must have happened during one of the package upgrades that are in updates-testing since Oct 5.
Version-Release number of selected component: xorg-x11-server-Xorg-1.19.0-0.1.20160929.fc25
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/libexec/Xorg vt2 -displayfd 3 -auth /run/user/1001/gdm/Xauthority -nolisten tcp -background none -noreset -keeptty -verbose 3 crash_function: dixRegisterPrivateKey executable: /usr/libexec/Xorg global_pid: 1493 kernel: 4.8.0-0.rc7.git0.1.fc25.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 4089 D8F2 FDB1 9C98 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1001
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (10 frames) #4 dixRegisterPrivateKey at privates.c:385 #5 glamor_init at glamor.c:478 #6 ScreenInit at driver.c:1605 #7 AddGPUScreen at dispatch.c:3952 #8 xf86platformAddDevice at xf86platformBus.c:542 #9 NewGPUDeviceRequest at lnx_platform.c:195 #10 device_added at udev.c:131 #11 socket_handler at udev.c:363 #12 ospoll_wait at ospoll.c:412 #13 WaitForSomething at WaitFor.c:222

Oops, my bad, I just read the systemd update description, seems this bug should be fixed with this round of updates. Sorry about the noise.
